I"™<p>At this point it is sufficient to linearize the model to start designing the linear controller K. By linearing the model, we replace non-linear components (\(cos, sin, ^{2}, ^{3}, etc..\))</p>

<p>The goal is to keep the pendulum upward. According to the model, this configuration is associated with the state:</p>

<p>\(\theta = \theta_{0}, \alpha = 0, \theta_{dot} = 0, \alpha_{dot} = 0\).</p>

